&lt;p>If you are interested in more of a light reading, here&amp;rsquo;s a &lt;a href="https://blog.qutech.nl/2021/02/25/ready-set-measure/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">blog post by Sophie&lt;/a> about running a similar experiment (the three-node network from last year), giving you a peek into what it is like to run one of these!&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>üéõÔ∏è yamlpars</title><link>https://matpompili.github.io/project/yamlpars/</link><pubDate>Wed, 02 Mar 2022 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://matpompili.github.io/project/yamlpars/</guid><description>&lt;p>With &lt;strong>yamlpars&lt;/strong> you can save configurations and parameters to YAML files, in a structured and easy-to use way.&lt;/p>
